Paratype. 4. Mesothoracic sclerite, ventral: Bs—basisternum; Fs— furcasternum; Fsa—furcasternal arm; Fsp—furcasternal pit; Kes—katepisternum; Pfs—postfurcasternum; Prs—presternum; PPfs—prothoracic postfurcasternum; Sc—spinasternum; Tn—trochantin. 5–6. Abdominal tip, variation of the subgenital plate. 7. Vaginal complex (cleared) with genital opening, membranous genital cavity, inner tooth-shaped black sclerite.
